rComments: If you have to take an English class at UCSC, take one from Professor Keilen. He's one of the smartest and most dedicated professors on campus. He can come across as almost snobbish with his teaching, but he really cares about his students and how they read. He'll push you hard to perform well because he really WANTS you to succeed. 10/10
Sean was a GREAT teacher! I dozed off in class sometimes, but mainly because I took it at 9am and was still drowsy. He really does care for his students and makes an effort to help if you want it.

He was a great professor. He is so intelligent and helpful. I learned so much in his course and got a good grade.  He's not down for more than two absences, so you have to go to class, but it is definitely worth it.  Great professor and great experience. I have talked to many other students who have taken his courses and they all agree.

Keilen is well spoken, intelligent, and attentive. Even placing his considerable knowledge aside, he is both an understanding and engaging professor who guides his students through their own ideas about texts by assuming an astonishingly balanced Socratic role in the class room. Keilen is both a delight and a marvel.

Keilen is one of the best professors I've had at UCSC and he made the literature major worth it! He's very passionate and incredibly intelligent about Shakespeare and English canon. You'll learn a lot if you go to lectures and pay attention. His essay prompts aren't very hard either, just creative and intuitive.

Seminar style classes with Keilen are awesome. He definitely wants you to be a part of a discussion, rather than sitting listening to him lecture. He gave ample opportunity to redo assignments, but he also expected very high intellectual standards. His courses aren't reading heavy, but you need to read what is assigned.
Professor Keilen is fantastic!! Very enthusiastic about Shakespeare and teaching. Very approachable and friendly. Lots of reading, but a great class. Would definitely recommend taking!
